                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="15257575" author="stefania" created="Tue, 26 Apr 2016 05:09:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve started looking at this so I&apos;ll carry on. The problem is that since &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-10624&quot; title=&quot;Support UDT in CQLSSTableWriter&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-10624&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-10624&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; we are using &lt;tt&gt;TypeCodec&lt;/tt&gt; to serialize rather than &lt;tt&gt;TypeSerializer&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15257728" author="slebresne" created="Tue, 26 Apr 2016 08:22:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;If that&apos;s the case, that&apos;s certainly wrong but I would also expect that the generated sstable can&apos;t be properly read from C*. Do we have a hole in our testing or am I missing something?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15257767" author="stefania" created="Tue, 26 Apr 2016 08:53:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s this line &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/blob/trunk/src/java/org/apache/cassandra/io/sstable/CQLSSTableWriter.java#L171&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;. It used to be a decompose on the type and it is causing the increase in size. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We do have unit tests and they can read the sstables, see for example this one &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/blob/trunk/test/unit/org/apache/cassandra/io/sstable/CQLSSTableWriterTest.java#L341&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;.  Is it because &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/blob/trunk/src/java/org/apache/cassandra/io/sstable/CQLSSTableWriter.java#L235&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;tt&gt;rawAddRow&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/a&gt; adjust the format or because we already support it for UD functions?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To return to a decompose on the type, we need to somehow convert &lt;tt&gt;com.datastax.driver.core.UDTValue&lt;/tt&gt; to a BB. I&apos;m not sure what&apos;s the best way to do this without exposing BBs to the users.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15257787" author="slebresne" created="Tue, 26 Apr 2016 09:05:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;My bad, I was actually thinking of something else. I guess I&apos;m not surprised it works then, and I guess using &lt;tt&gt;TypeCodec&lt;/tt&gt; should be kind of correct. What I&apos;m missing then is why the file is bigger with that change (since both &lt;tt&gt;TypeCodec&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;TypeSerializer&lt;/tt&gt; should produce the same thing), assuming that change is indeed the issue of course?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15257809" author="stefania" created="Tue, 26 Apr 2016 09:22:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I agree, &lt;tt&gt;TypeCodec&lt;/tt&gt; is correct because then &lt;tt&gt;rawAddRow&lt;/tt&gt; calls the insert statement &lt;tt&gt;addUpdateForKey()&lt;/tt&gt;, which will then binds the parameters and so forth. I&apos;ve definitely verified that if I change that line back then the size of the sstable returns as small as it was before. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ll investigate why &lt;tt&gt;TypeCodec&lt;/tt&gt; produces a different size then, rather than trying to re-instate &lt;tt&gt;TypeSerializer&lt;/tt&gt;, thanks. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15257864" author="stefania" created="Tue, 26 Apr 2016 10:25:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The size difference was due to delta time encoding, the BB generated by either &lt;tt&gt;TypeCodec&lt;/tt&gt; or &lt;tt&gt;TypeSerializer&lt;/tt&gt; are indeed identical. However, &lt;tt&gt;TypeCodec&lt;/tt&gt; was taking twice as long to serialize values due to the time taken to convert a column spec into a &lt;tt&gt;TypeCodec&lt;/tt&gt;. I&apos;ve cached the type codecs and now the time and output size are the same as for &lt;tt&gt;TypeSerializer&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&apos;table-wrap&apos;&gt;
&lt;table class=&apos;confluenceTable&apos;&gt;&lt;tbody&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;th class=&apos;confluenceTh&apos;&gt;trunk&lt;/th&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td class=&apos;confluenceTd&apos;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/stef1927/cassandra/commits/11646&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;patch&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td class=&apos;confluenceTd&apos;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://cassci.datastax.com/view/Dev/view/stef1927/job/stef1927-11646-testall/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;testall&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td class=&apos;confluenceTd&apos;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://cassci.datastax.com/view/Dev/view/stef1927/job/stef1927-11646-dtest/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;dtest&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/tbody&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;p&gt;CI pending. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Note: we should probably remove the unit test before committing, since it takes about 25 seconds to run. I&apos;ve left it there for reviewing or further debugging.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15258004" author="ifesdjeen" created="Tue, 26 Apr 2016 12:39:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 on the patch&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;pre-10624 code takes 27394 milliseconds and consumes &lt;tt&gt;65.734.403 bytes (65,7 MB on disk)&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
current trunk takes 35388 milliseconds and consumes &lt;tt&gt;70.551.042 bytes (70,6 MB on disk)&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
and &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/stef1927/cassandra/commits/11646&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;patched version&lt;/a&gt; takes 25541 milliseconds and consumes &lt;tt&gt;64.994.448 bytes (65 MB on disk)&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(ran all versions several times, and their layout in terms of performance is similar (pre-10624 and patched versions are closer together, while trunk takes longer and has a larger size)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15258007" author="ifesdjeen" created="Tue, 26 Apr 2016 12:40:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Test failures seem unrelated. I&apos;ve set the patch to &quot;ready to commit&quot; however, I&apos;d as Stefania said, also remove the test as it runs longer and requires manual checking. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15259316" author="stefania" created="Wed, 27 Apr 2016 01:22:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thank you for the review and for testing.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Committed to trunk without the unit test as 29d4a8297905463e4f0bb28fe0b4cc354dc1a0ab.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
